The paper discusses the use of symmetric cryptography for security services in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The focus on key predistribution schemes and the use of combinatorial designs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the discussion of the lack of central infrastructure and the need for distributed solutions may make the paper relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
